<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/183> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #183" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 3.5.3; Münzer, Gent. Val. 35, no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/162> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #162" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.61.1; Diod. 11.69.1; Dion. Hal. 9.51.1; Chr. 354 (Potito II et Mamerco); Fast. Hyd. (Emilio et Valerio); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 91, 358f. Valerius fought the Aequi and Aemilius the Sabines (Liv. 2.62.1-4; Dion. Hal. 9.55.1-4). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 35, no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/161> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #161" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name Valerius, see 483. Diodorus has the cognomen Poplicola. Aemilius' cognomen Mamercus is preserved in Diod. and Chr. 354 on both 470 and 467. Dion. Hal. (9.51.4) calls the Consul's father Lucius but the Consul Tiberius (9.51.1, and 59.1). Livy has Titus both years, but Diod. has Titus in 470 and Tiberius in 467." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/110> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #110" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.42.7; Diod. 11.41.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - -] Potitus); Dion. Hal. 8.87.2, with filiation, and 88.1; Chr. 354 (Vivulano et Potito); Fast. Hyd. (Fabio et Volesio); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 89, 354f. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 35, no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/109> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #109" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Dion. Hal. Fabius' cognomen is Silanus or Silvanus. On Valerius, see CIL 1(2), p. 190. Diod. reads {Gr} for Potitus. Degrassi (89) rearranges the family tree, and drops the cognomen Volusus, which however is retained in RE (see col. 2318)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/106> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #106" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prosecuted Sp. Cassius for perduellio, and secured his condemnation (Liv. 2.41.11; Dion. Hal. 8.77.2-80.1; cf. 82.3, and 87.2; Piso, fr. 37, Peter; Cic. Dom. 101; Rep. 2.49 and 60; Lael. 28 and 36; Phil. 2.114; Liv. 4.15.4; Diod. 11.37.7; Val. Max. 5.8.2; 6.3.1; Flor. 1.17.7; Dio fr. 19; Zon. 7.17). On these Quaestors, see Mommsen, Str. 2.537ff.; Latte, TAPhA 67 (1936) 24ff. On Valerius, see CIL 1\n     .1, p. 190; Münzer, Gent. Val. 49, no. 44." .
